									<p>
										<span class="image left"><img src="images/avatar5.png" alt="" /></span>
										Welcome to my homepage! I am a Lecturer at the  School of Computer Science and Engineering, International University, VNU-HCM, Vietnam since Feb-2023. 
									</p>
									<p>
										Before joining HCMIU, I spent eight years at the University of Sussex, UK, as a Research Fellow in Psychology (2018-2022) at the <a href="http://www.sussex.ac.uk/psychology/sibg/" target="_blank"> Sussex Ingestive Behaviour Group (SIBG)</a>, School of Psychology and a Research Fellow in Multisensory Experiences (2015-2018) at the <a href="http://www.sussex.ac.uk/schi/" target="_blank">Sussex Human-Computer Interaction (SCHI /sky/) Lab</a>, School of Engineering and Informatics. Before that, I was a Research Fellow in Shape-Chainging Interface (2014-2015) at Bristol Interaction Group, School of Engineering, University of Bristol, UK. 
									</p>
									<p>
										I received my PhD in Computer Science in 2014 and my MSc in Advance Computing: Internet Technologies with Security in 2008, both from University of Bristol, 
										while I was working with <a href="https://uclic.ucl.ac.uk/people/sriram-subramanian" target="_blank">Prof. Sriram Subramanian</a>. 
										I received my BSc in Electronics and Telecommunications at Hanoi University of Science and Technology in 2006.
									</p>
									
									<h2>Research Interest</h2>
									<p>My research interest falls into the Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) multidisciplinary domain, where there is a cross feeding between Computer Science, Multisensory Experience, Brain Computer Interface, Eating Behaviour, and Experimental Psychology. I am interested in building interactive systems with novel technology to enhance human-computer interaction bandwidth and enrich user experience.
									</p>
									<p>
									Some of my works have been covered on popular channels such as 
									<a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09fgdxm" target="_blank">BBC Click</a>, 
									<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sSglcz8TIAU&t=3s" target="_blank">ITV Good Morning Britain</a>, 
									<a href="https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/don-t-scoff-flying-food-is-a-taste-of-the-future-marianna-obrist-qw2qx6x3l" target="_blank">The Times</a>, 
									<a href="https://www.digitaltrends.com/cool-tech/levitating-food-sussex/" target="_blank">Digital Trends</a>, 
									<a href="https://www.standard.co.uk/reveller/restaurants/borough-market-to-host-uk-s-first-food-tech-village-popup-a3668626.html" target="_blank">The Evening Standard</a>, 
									<a href="https://spectrum.ieee.org/tastyfloats-a-levitating-food-delivery-system" target="_blank">IEEE Spectrum</a>, 
									<a href="https://www.wired.co.uk/article/tate-sensorium-review-2015" target="_blank">WIRED</a>, 
									<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2015/aug/22/tate-sensorium-art-soundscapes-chocolates-invisible-rain" target="_blank">The Guardian</a> 
									and in different languages (i.e., English, French, German, Japanese, <a href="http://khoahoc.tv/thuc-an-lo-lung--phat-kien-moi-de-thu-hut-nhung-nguoi-ham-cua-la-90685" target="_blank">Vietnamese</a>, Chinese, and Russian).

									<p>
									<b>Keywords:</b> Human-Computer Interaction, User experience, Brain Computer Interface, Multisensory Interaction (touch, taste, smell), Human-Food Interaction, Flavour perception, Sense of Agency.									
									</p>
